President Donald Trump and First Lady Melania Trump attended the AMVETS Post 44 Salute to American Heroes event in Struthers, Ohio. President Trump gave remarks on the reform of the Department of Veterans Affairs and honored World War II veteran Robert M. Bishop. He discussed the progress and reformation of the Department of Veterans Affairs and vowed to protect those who protect the country. Mr. Bishop, who served as a gunner aboard the USS Tennessee during the attack on Pearl Harbor, was presented with a Certificate of Recognition for his heroism. President Trump thanked all veterans, stating that their courage and patriotism is the strength of the nation. The event was part of American Heroes Week at the White House, which celebrates and honors military service members, veterans, law enforcement officers, first responders, and workers.